snippet.textDisplay:
Congratulations to the performers. Extra credit goes to strong vocal. 
I know people like songs which will give them rhythm and power. But at the end of the day the question is , what is coke studio trying to achieve. If Coke Studio wants to remake all good authentic songs into a fusion/disco/rock/electro song then they have done a good job. But then again, Gaan Bangla and Fusion studio already has done them and it is nothing new in my ears. But if Coke Studio want to produce something unique, then they have to really get inside these precious songs and amalgamate music into the words. Rock guitar, drum rolls, bass punch these are all for performance; but we need pure music with depth in it which will sound out of the ordinary.
